               <msContents>
                  <summary>I) Maṣḥafa krǝstǝnna “Book of the Christening” (fols. 3r-36v)
 
                     Colophon.</summary>
                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i1">

                     <incipit>
                        <foreign xml:lang="en"/>
                     </incipit>
                     <explicit>
                        <foreign xml:lang="en"/>
                     </explicit>
                     <note/>
                  </msItem>
                  
                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i2">
                     <note>- Text I is called Maṣḥafa ṭǝmqat in Additio 1 (<locus target="#36v">36v</locus>).</note>
                  </msItem>
                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i3">
                     <colophon xml:id="coloph1">
                        <locus target="#36v">36v</locus>, l. 4: ተፈጸመ፡ መጽሐፈ፡ ጥምቀት፡ በሰላመ፡ እግዚአብሔር፡
                        አሜን። ዛቲ፡ መጽሐፍ፡ ዘቅዱስ፡ ሚካኤል፡ እንባ፡ ሐረሳ፡ ዘአድ፡ ሕያው፡ በዘመኑ፡ ዘአጽሐፋ፡ ቀሲስ፡ ፍሥሐ፡ ጊዮርጊስ።
                        ወገበዙሂ [lac.] ከማሁ፡ ይጽሐፍ፡ ስሞሙ፡ ኀበ፡ ዓምደ፡ ወርቅ፡ በቀለመ፡ ጽድቅ፡ ለዓለመ፡ ዓለም፡ ወጸሐፈሁኒ፡
                        ኃጥእ፡ ዘድንግል። The colophon states that the Ms. was owned by the church Dabra
                        Mikāʾel ʾƎnba Ḥarisay (Mikāʾel ʿAd Ḥǝyaw). It mentions also the
                        commissioner, Fǝśśǝḥa Giyorgis, and the scribe, <persName role="scribe" ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS11077Zadengel">Za-Dǝngǝl</persName>. </colophon>
                  </msItem>
               </msContents>
